#MeetTheNewCrew

Sarah Speckhart is a recent graduate of Salve Regina University where she received a Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Elementary Education and minor in Special Education. Her goal as an educator is to instill valuable lessons that children will carry throughout their years of learning and beyond. Sara firmly believes in the potential and ability of all learners and is dedicated to creating a positive and productive learning environment where scholars learn to take academic risks and truly thrive. In her free time, you can find Sarah coaching her town's swim team, traveling, reading a good book, or spending time with her friends and family. Sarah is so excited to share her passion for learning with the Cresthaven community.

Cassandra is eager to serve the Plainfield community and teach the scholars of Cresthaven Academy.

post_text:
#MeetTheNewCrew

Hope Bera joins the Cresthaven team as a recent graduate of Drew University. She holds a Masters degree in Teaching K-6 and an endorsement in Special Education. Also an active member of the Teaching Honor Society, Kappa Delta Pi, Hope knew from the age of 5 that she wanted to be a teacher. As a child she snuck the kitchen chairs into her bedroom where she would set up stuffed to listen to her lessons. Hope brings to Cresthaven a wide range of experiences, including working with kindergarteners; mentoring high schoolers; and helping incarcerated men pass their GED. Hope is eager to instill her love of learning in the scholars at Cresthaven.

#MeetTheNewCrew

Cristina Benedicto graduated from Kean University in 2017 with a Bachelor's Degree in Early Childhood Education with a concentration in English writing. Prior to working at Cresthaven Academy, Cristina taught English to students living in Tokyo, Japan. Driven by the belief that every child has a voice to be heard, in Cristina‚Äôs classroom each scholar will achieve their voice and grow in academic success. Cristina is enthusiastic to begin her career at Cresthaven Academy and looks forward to nurturing, guiding, and growing with the scholars and families of Plainfield. In her spare time, she enjoys reading a good book, traveling to new sights, and cherishing moments with her family and friends.

#MeetTheNewCrew

Rebecca Witt is the music teacher at Cresthaven Academy. She earned a Bachelors of Music Education and Masters of Arts in Teaching from Westminster Choir College of Rider University. She has five years of teaching experience in diverse settings, including teaching English abroad in Thailand. Rebecca is passionate about educating the whole child and believes that students learn best by doing. When she is not teaching, you can find Miss Witt learning to cook new meals, going for bike rides, and travelling around the world. Rebecca is extremely honored to be a part of the Cresthaven family.

Megan Brower is a recent graduate of West Chester University. She holds a Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Early Childhood Education and Special Education. Megan has worked closely with children in the Special Education community and has even traveled outside of the country to share her love of teaching with Special Education students and families around the world. Megan is passionate about guiding children to grow and succeed both inside and outside of the classroom and looks forward to bringing that passion to Cresthaven as a Special Education Teacher. When she is not teaching, Megan enjoys volunteering at the local soup kitchen, traveling, playing with her two pugs, and spending time with friends and family.

At Cresthaven Academy, we believe that all children, regardless of race or economic status, can succeed when given equal access to a high quality education. Now, more than ever, the tools to access education are of critical importance as our school community navigates the challenges of remote learning. We know that many families are facing daily hardships that make learning from home nearly impossible. Cresthaven remains committed to educating the #WholeChild in the midst of these uncertain times by providing daily meals, tablets and chromebooks, emotional and mental-health support, as well as meeting basic needs like diapers and toilet paper wherever we can. This #GivingTuesdayNow you can make a difference and shape our future with a gift to Cresthaven.

https://cresthavenacademy.z2systems.com/np/clients/cresthavenacademy/donation.jsp

post_text:
#MeetTheTeam Danielle Malysa

Danielle Malysa is the School Social Worker at Cresthaven Academy Charter School. Prior to working at Cresthaven Academy, Danielle worked on a crisis unit at Saint Clare‚Äôs hospital. She has worked with a variety of populations, including at-risk children needing assistance during a crisis. Danielle holds a School Social Work Certificate and a License in Social Work from the state of New Jersey. She graduated from Rutgers University with a Masters in School Work, and received a Bachelors in Psychology from the University of Delaware. Danielle is excited to join the Cresthaven team and provide support for the children and families in Plainfield.

post_text:
#MeetTheTeam Thao Le

Thao Le is a First Grade Teacher at Cresthaven Academy Charter School. She attended Montclair State University and graduated with a B.A in Family and Child Studies in 2012. In 2018, she obtained her M.A.T. at Relay Graduate School of Education. Prior to teaching, Thao worked at the Division of Child Protection and Permanency. She started her path in teaching in 2016 at Newark Uncommon Schools as a First Grade Teacher. Passionate about closing the achievement gap, Thao is delighted to bring her excitement and joy for teaching to Cresthaven Academy. When she is not teaching, you can find her catching up with her past scholars, spending time with family and friends, as well as her Boston Terrier, Frank Castle.

post_text:
#MeetTheTeam Christina Munoz

Christina Munoz is a Special Education Teacher at Cresthaven Academy. She graduated from Brooklyn College with a B.A. in Early Childhood and Special Education. She also holds a Masters Degree from Concordia University in Curriculum and Instruction with an extension in Special Education. Her passion has always been to teach the next generation the necessary social and academic skills to pursue their dreams. Christina believes that teaching is not just a job - it is a special interaction with a scholar who has a great purpose and talents that must be nurtured. She is eager to engage the Cresthaven scholars inside the classroom by introducing them to new concepts backed by critical thinking. In her free time, Christina enjoys spending time with her family and friends, attending church services and spontaneously venturing out for a weekend getaway.

#MeetTheTeam Eduard Manvelyan

Eduard Manvelyan is Cresthaven Academy‚Äôs Music Teacher. After earning his Bachelors of Arts degree in Music from The College of Staten Island, Eduard worked as a professional musician and a music tutor. He believes that, through music, he can encourage his music students, build their self confidence, and to teach them to value the work they do in school. Eduard is delighted to share his love and passion for music with the Cresthaven community. When he is not teaching, Eduard enjoys writing music and spending time with family and friends.

#MeetTheTeam: Ashley Ramirez

Ashley Ramirez is a Resource Room teacher at Cresthaven Academy. She holds a Bachelors of Arts degree in Elementary Education with an endorsement as a Teacher of Students with Disabilities, and a co-concentration of mathematics from Bloomfield College. Ashley brings experience as a 3rd grade in-class support teacher in the South Orange/Maplewood Public school district, where she worked closely with the child study team and students with disabilities. Aside from teaching, Ashley loves watching and playing soccer, spending time with family and friends, and traveling the world. Ashley is excited to join the Cresthaven family and to share her passion for education with the families and scholars of the Cresthaven community.

post_text:
#MeetTheTeam: Michelle Feliciano

Michelle Feliciano serves as Operations Support Assistant at Cresthaven Academy. She was born in Newark, New Jersey and raised in Puerto Rico by her grandparents. It is there that she developed a passion to serve others. Motivated by her desire to serve the community, Michelle obtained her medical assistant certification and spent over three years working with a medical practice in Puerto Rico. Michelle currently serves the community of Plainfield through her work at Cresthaven, as well as being active in community outreach, where she is a dedicated leader in youth, children, and worship ministries. Michelle aspires to continue her education in counseling to help others overcome obstacles and fulfill their personal journeys in meaningful ways. Michelle enjoys laughing, making new friends, and spending quality time building memories with family and friends.

#MeetTheTeam: Leanna Caswell

Leanna Caswell is a recent graduate of Seton Hall University. She has a Bachelor's of Science in Elementary/Special Education, with a focus in Social and Behavioral Sciences and a minor in Social Work. Leanna has worked closely with students with a wide range of abilities and has had a deep passion for the Special Education community since high school. When she is not teaching, Leanna enjoys trying new foods, running errands, spending time with friends and family, walking her Great Dane, and being with her kitten! Leanna is eager to share her love of learning with Cresthaven scholars and families, and to have the opportunity to evolve and grow as a 2nd grade teacher with the support of the Cresthaven community.

#MeetTheTeam: Brianna Norcross

Brianna Norcross is a Kindergarten teacher at Cresthaven Academy. Brianna is a recent graduate from Rowan University where she earned her B.A. in Elementary Education and American Studies with an endorsement of Teacher of Students with Disabilities. After spending the 2018-19 school year as a Clinical Intern in a Kindergarten classroom in Camden, New Jersey, Brianna is excited to bring her educational and professional experience to the scholars and families of Cresthaven. Driven by a desire to instill and encourage student diversity and individual needs, Brianna is passionate about ensuring that every scholar has the foundation for success and growth in and out of the classroom. When she is not teaching, Brianna enjoys cooking, working out, and spending time with her family and friends.

#MeetTheTeam: Johnny Vega

Johnny Vega grew up in Brooklyn New York and moved to Kearny, New Jersey where he attended Kearny High School and was a student athlete who graduated with honors. Awarded an athletic scholarship for Division II Men's Cross Country, Johnny continued his education at Bloomfield College, where he graduated with a Bachelor's Degree in Elementary Education with a concentration in mathematics. Johnny joins the Cresthaven team with 2 years of experience teaching 1st and 2nd grades, and is thrilled to continue his career with the Cresthaven Family as a 1st grade teacher. Johnny‚Äôs passion is to educate, motivate, and impact scholars by empowering them to reach for their goals! Johnny truly believes that there is no such thing a dream too big, and he desires that each of his scholars will dream big and work for his or her successes! When he is not teaching, Johnny enjoys running, rain or shine, and hanging out with friends and family.

#MeetTheTeam: Alexe Rumble

Ali Rumble is a 3rd grade teacher at Cresthaven Academy. Growing up in Charlotte, North Carolina Ali attended a charter school for most of her elementary through middle school career. In 2016, Ali graduated from Appalachian State University with a bachelor's degree in elementary education. With three years of teaching experience in both North Carolina and Florida, Ali recently relocated to New Jersey and is eager to make a difference in the lives of the scholars and families of Cresthaven and the Plainfield community at large.

#MeetTheTeam: Naomi Joseph

Naomi Joseph is a 3rd grade teacher at Cresthaven Academy Charter School. She received her B.A. in Psychology from Rutgers University and her M.Ed. from Emmanuel College in Massachusetts. Previously, Naomi was a preschool teacher in Fanwood before teaching 3rd grade for two years in the Boston Public School District. Naomi is excited to be back in her home state and serving the Plainfield community at Cresthaven. Passionate about student growth, Ms. Joseph is determined and dedicated to help all of her scholars grow their love of learning! When out of the classroom, you can find Naomi working out, cooking new recipes, trying new foods or traveling to new places.

post_text:
#MeetTheTeam: Megan Gerity

Megan Gerity is currently the Director of Curriculum and Instruction at Cresthaven Academy Charter School. She received her B.S. and M.A.T. in Urban Early Childhood Education/ESL from The College of New Jersey as well as her endorsement for supervisor certification from Rutgers University. Megan has served as the kindergarten grade team lead here at Cresthaven. Prior to Cresthaven, Megan taught first grade and pre-kindergarten in Newark,NJ where she was also a grade team lead and instructional coach. Megan was a teacher trainer for the National Institute for Early Education Research, where she worked with K-3 teachers across the state on utilizing developmentally appropriate practices in their classrooms. Outside of school, she enjoys traveling, cooking, reading, and spending time with family and friends. Megan is eager to support teachers in creating a rigorous and positive school experience for the scholars of Plainfield!

Four years ago, our Founding Team began their work to bring the vision of Cresthaven Academy to life. A school with high academic standards wrapped in a whole lot of love is not an easy thing to build or maintain, but through the hard work of our families, staff, and scholars, we've created something truly special.

We are so excited to premiere our End of Year video at tomorrow's kindergarten graduation! Here's a sneak peek at what Year 3 looked like at Cresthaven Academy.

Field trips matter.

‚Äú...a flurry of recent studies shows a range of benefits from cultural experiences‚Äîsome as minimal as going to see one play or spending half a day at an art museum. Researchers led by University of Arkansas professor Jay P. Greene have found that those experiences increase students‚Äô tolerance, empathy, and ability to understand life in another time and place, as measured by survey questions. The effects are strongest for disadvantaged students, perhaps because it‚Äôs their first exposure to a museum or live theater.‚Äù (Forbes 2019)

3 years. 36 teachers. 234 families. 351 hours. 1,404 conferences. 100% attendance, 100% of the time.

We are shouting it from the roof top because we just reached 100% attendance at our final round of Parent-Teacher Conferences for the year! This means that, out of the 9 rounds of conferences we have held since Cresthaven Academy opened its doors, all 9 of them have had 100% attendance from parents. Thank you to all of the staff, scholars, and especially families for making it possible.

post_text:
At Cresthaven Academy, we believe that the pathway to college begins at kindergarten. In keeping with this belief, we take our scholars to visit a new college campus every spring so that they can learn firsthand about the academic programs, extracurricular activities, and career pathways each one offers.

This year our 2nd graders had the honor of visiting Princeton University, their very first Ivy League school. They learned that with enough grit, they may one day join the ranks of Princeton alumni such as First Lady Michelle Obama, Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor, and President John F. Kennedy.

The future is bright.

#collegebeginsatkindergarten #collegebeginsatcresthaven

post_text:
Our school is founded on the belief that all children, regardless of race or economic status, can succeed when given equal access to a high-quality education. In order to provide that access to all New Jersey students, their parents must have the ability to seek out the best educational option for their child, regardless of what zip code they happen to live in.

This #CharterAwarenessWeek, the families, staff, and scholars of Cresthaven Academy stand committed to promoting excellent schools for all children - whether it's traditional, private, vocational-technical, or charter. When we work together, we can ensure that every student in the state has access to a quality curriculum, fully supported teachers, and options for post-secondary pathways.

#AllSchoolsOneFamily Craig J. Coughlin Steve Sweeney Governor Phil Murphy

"Life's most persistent and urgent question is, 'What are you doing for others?'"
